<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="28" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="11.[136,1452,446,940]" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,527,698,724]" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">Distribution and ecology:—</emphasis>
The species occurs from the western 
<collectingCountry box="[964,1257,698,724]" name="United States of America" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">United States of America</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[1300,1399,699,725]" name="Uruguay" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">Uruguay</collectingCountry>
, has records in the five regions of 
<collectingCountry box="[472,540,734,760]" name="Brazil" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">Brazil</collectingCountry>
in all its phytogeographic domains (
<bibRefCitation author="Flora do Brasil" box="[956,1196,734,760]" pageId="11" pageNumber="28" refId="ref15971" refString="Flora do Brasil 2020 (2020) Fabaceae. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. [http: // reflora. jbrj. gov. br / reflora / floradobrasil / FB 115]" type="url" year="2020">
Flora do 
<collectingCountry box="[1061,1128,734,760]" name="Brazil" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">Brasil</collectingCountry>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
), associated with open and anthropogenic environments with invasive plant behavior (Queiroz; Loiola, 2009; Dantas; Silva, 2013, 
<bibRefCitation author="Souto, F. S. &amp; Quaresma, A. A. &amp; Queiroz, R. T. &amp; Pereira, M. S." pageId="11" pageNumber="28" pagination="18 - 39" refId="ref18928" refString="Souto, F. S., Quaresma, A. A., Queiroz, R. T. &amp; Pereira, M. S. (2019) Estudo taxonomico da Tribo Cassieae (Leguminosae - Caesalpinioideae) no Parque Ecologico Engenheiro Avidos, Cajazeiras-PB. Pesquisa e Ensino em Ciencias Exatas e da Natureza 3 (1): 18 - 39. https: // doi. org / 10.29215 / pecen. v 3 i 1.1146" type="journal article" year="2019">
Souto 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">et al.</emphasis>
2019
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[136,1452,446,940]" box="[189,825,842,869]" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,351,842,868]" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">Phenology:—</emphasis>
Registered with flowers and fruits in May.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="28" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[136,1452,446,940]" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,490,878,904]" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">Taxonomic discussion:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Greene" authorityYear="1899" baseAuthorityName="Persoon" baseAuthorityYear="1805" box="[490,791,878,904]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Chamaecrista" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="11" pageNumber="28" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rotundifolia">
<emphasis box="[490,791,878,904]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">Chamaecrista rotundifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be recognized by the absence of nectary, bifoliolate leaves, asymmetrical pedicel flowers, dialypetalous corolla.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
